KNN Classificação¶

In [17]:
srand(0)
m = 500
x = rand(m, 2)
y = [x[i,1].^2 + x[i,2].^2 + randn() * 0.05 > 0.3 ? 1.0 : 0.0 for i = 1:m]
P = find(y .== 1)
N = find(y .== 0)
scatter(x[P,1], x[P,2], c=:red, leg=false, m=(stroke(1), 3))
scatter!(x[N,1], x[N,2], c=:blue, leg=false, m=(stroke(1), 3))
xlims!(-0.05, 1.05)
ylims!(-0.05, 1.05)
Out[17]:
  • Dado um novo dado $x^0$;
  • Dado um valor $k$;
  • A classe de $x^0$ escolhida olhando para os $k$ dados mais prximos e escolhendo a classe de maior frequncia.
In [22]:
using Interact

@manipulate for a = linspace(0, 1, 101), b = linspace(0, 1, 101)
    P = find(y .== 1)
    N = find(y .== 0)
    scatter(x[P,1], x[P,2], c=:red, leg=false, m=(stroke(0), 3))
    scatter!(x[N,1], x[N,2], c=:blue, leg=false, m=(stroke(0), 3))

    k = 5
    x_novo = [a; b]
    D = [norm(x_novo - x[i,:]) for i = 1:m]
    I = sortperm(D)[1:k]
    reds = blues = 0
    for i = I
        c = if y[i] == 1
            reds += 1
            :red
        else
            blues += 1
            :blue
        end
        plot!([x_novo[1], x[i,1]], [x_novo[2], x[i,2]], c=c, l=:dash)
    end
    (c, c2) = reds > blues ? (:red,:pink) : (:blue,:lightblue)
    scatter!([x_novo[1]], [x_novo[2]], m=(stroke(1,:black),c2), ms=5)

    xlims!(-0.05, 1.05)
    ylims!(-0.05, 1.05)
end

function knn_class(x, y, x_novo; k = 3)
    m = length(y)
    D = [norm(x_novo - x[i,:]) for i = 1:m]
    I = sortperm(D)[1:k]
    
    classes = unique(y)
    cc = [count(y[I] .== c) for c = classes]
    return classes[indmax(cc)]
end

KNN - regressão¶

In [7]:
function knn_reg(x, y, x_novo; k = 3, w=x -> 1.0)
    n = size(x, 2)
    m = length(y)
    D = if n == 1
        [abs(x_novo - x[i]) for i = 1:m]
    else
        [norm(x_novo - x[i,:]) for i = 1:m]
    end
    
    I = sortperm(D)[1:k]
    W = n == 1 ? [norm(x_novo - x[I[i]]) for i = 1:k] : [norm(x_novo - x[I[i],:]) for i = 1:k]
    W .= w.(W)
    return dot(y[I], W) / sum(W)
end
